General.Name: iShares S&P 500 Value ETF
General.Description: The index measures the performance of the large-capitalization value sector of the U.S. equity market. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents.
